body: Hi farzane, This issue is because you used "Honeybee_Generate Zone Test Points" with multiple surfaces instead of an honeybee zone. Only the second branch is right, thus if you select it your simulation should be fine. [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/la2V-cBKompgavhSCNuSg0lZma2Im4Twh9gBZVZrLpR823I7FwjSLxNroYDsKTlsDlOIr0GyvARIqxZ0P-IcG7l-0AIYv1XE/01.png) [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/la2V-cBKomql1gT22kdtS8-dBu9-wZ9wChJ-6uvpdU8-w0KEe9XNACjyNQ7BhgUmADFr9pKUoMGyZyEPbhQSosDpi8IeQi7g/02.png) I suggest that you use "Honeybee_Generate Zone Test Points" with a closed honeybee zone. [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/la2V-cBKomrX0H14X9xVfZIEynW1qr642TMEO*KuOLUQa8zjmeSG1DZD8usZMWASmNpQKFYUgrshF7I2UxDM-rPkCR4UVWp5/01_b.png) Best Antonello
